#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.99"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.99:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.99:0.2"
msgid "10. Pupphavagga"
msgstr "10. Flowers"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 99. Gaddulabaddhasutta → gaddula (or bhaddula) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.99:0.3"
msgid "99. Gaddulabaddhasutta"
msgstr "99. A Leash"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.150"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.99:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.2"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro."
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.3"
msgid ""
"Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ."
msgstr ""
"No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, "
"hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.4"
msgid ""
"Hoti so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ mahāsamuddo ussussati visussati na bhavati;"
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when the ocean dries up and evaporates and is no more."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.5"
msgid ""
"na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"But still, I say, there is no making an end of suffering for sentient beings "
"roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.6"
msgid ""
"Hoti so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ sineru pabbatarājā ḍayhati vinassati na "
"bhavati;"
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when Sineru the king of mountains is burned up and "
"destroyed, and is no more."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.7"
msgid ""
"na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"But still, I say, there is no making an end of suffering for sentient beings "
"roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.8"
msgid ""
"Hoti so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ mahāpathavī ḍayhati vinassati na bhavati;"
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when the great earth is burned up and destroyed, and is "
"no more."

msgctxt "sn22.99:1.9"
msgid ""
"na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"But still, I say, there is no making an end of suffering for sentient beings "
"roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

# sā (= Skt śvan) is a short form for “dog”. Masculine!
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: gaddulabaddho → gaddūlabandho (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn22.99:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sā gaddulabaddho daḷhe khīle vā thambhe vā "
"upanibaddho tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā anuparidhāvati anuparivattati;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a dog on a leash was tethered to a strong post or pillar. It would "
"just keep running and circling around that post or pillar."

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the "
"noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in their teaching. They’ve "
"not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in their teaching."

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.3"
msgid "sappurisadhamme avinīto rūpaṃ attato samanupassati … pe …"
msgstr "They regard form …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.4"
msgid "vedanaṃ attato samanupassati …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.5"
msgid "saññaṃ attato samanupassati …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre attato samanupassati …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.7"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā viññāṇaṃ, "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.8"
msgid ""
"So rūpaññeva anuparidhāvati anuparivattati, vedanaññeva … pe … saññaññeva … "
"saṅkhāreyeva … viññāṇaññeva anuparidhāvati anuparivattati."
msgstr ""
"They just keep running and circling around form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.9"
msgid ""
"So rūpaṃ anuparidhāvaṃ anuparivattaṃ, vedanaṃ … pe … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … "
"viññāṇaṃ anuparidhāvaṃ anuparivattaṃ, na parimuccati rūpamhā, na parimuccati "
"vedanāya, na parimuccati saññāya, na parimuccati saṅkhārehi, na parimuccati "
"viññāṇamhā, na parimuccati jātiyā jarāmaraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"Doing so, they’re not freed from form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness. They’re not freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from "
"sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn22.99:2.10"
msgid "‘Na parimuccati dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "They’re not freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.99:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī … pe … "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto, "
msgstr ""
"An educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and "
"trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and "
"are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.2"
msgid "na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati … pe …"
msgstr "They don’t regard form …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.3"
msgid "na vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.4"
msgid "na saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.5"
msgid "na saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.6"
msgid ""
"na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; na attani vā "
"viññāṇaṃ, na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"or consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in "
"self, or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.7"
msgid ""
"So rūpaṃ nānuparidhāvati nānuparivattati, vedanaṃ … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … "
"viññāṇaṃ nānuparidhāvati nānuparivattati."
msgstr ""
"They don’t keep running and circling around form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.8"
msgid ""
"So rūpaṃ ananuparidhāvaṃ ananuparivattaṃ, vedanaṃ … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … "
"viññāṇaṃ ananuparidhāvaṃ ananuparivattaṃ; parimuccati rūpamhā, parimuccati "
"vedanāya, parimuccati saññāya, parimuccati saṅkhārehi, parimuccati "
"viññāṇamhā, parimuccati jātiyā jarāmaraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"By not doing so, they’re freed from form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness. They’re freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn22.99:3.9"
msgid "‘Parimuccati dukkhasmā’ti vadāmī”ti."
msgstr "They’re freed from suffering, I say.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.99:3.10"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
